Boil the @water{300%ml}(for the rice) in a large #saucepan{} over high heat. Add a pinch of @salt{} and @Chinese five spice{1/2}. When boiling, stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from the heat and set aside (still covered) for another ~{10%minutes}.

> TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into small pieces. Trim the @carrot{1}, then halve and grate on a #coarse grater{} (no need to peel). Trim the @courgette{1}, quarter lengthways and chop widthways into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop the @beef strips{240%g} into a #mixing bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and sprinkle on the @plain flour{8%g}. Use your hands to make sure the steak has a light coating of flour. Keep to one side.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Heat a #frying pan{} over medium heat and add the @desiccated coconut{25%g}. Cook until golden, stirring frequently, ~{2-3%minutes}. Transfer to a #small bowl{} and return the pan to high heat. Add a splash of @oil{1%splash} and the pepper and courgette. Stir-fry until softened and browned at the edges, ~{4-5%minutes}. Transfer to a #bowl{} (we will add them back in later).

Keep the frying pan on high heat and add another splash of @oil{1%splash}. Add the steak and stir-fry until golden on all sides, ~{2-3%minutes}. Lower the heat to medium and add the garlic and the rest of the @Chinese five spice{1/2}. Cook for another ~{1%minute} then add the @soy sauce{50%ml} and @mirin{15%ml} to the pan. Simmer the sauce until starting to thicken, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Return the cooked veggies to the pan and heat until piping hot, ~{1%minute}. Fluff the rice up with a #fork{} and stir through the grated carrot. Share between your plates and top with the steak stir-fry. Finish with a sprinkling of the desiccated coconut. Enjoy!